  "prompt": "What is the best pre workout drink before a long run?",
  "response": "The best pre-workout drink before a long run can vary depending on individual preferences, dietary restrictions, and specific energy needs, but here are some common options that are generally effective:\n\n1. **Electrolyte Drinks**: Drinks like Gatorade or Tailwind are designed to replenish electrolytes lost through sweat and provide carbohydrates for energy. They can help maintain hydration and energy levels during long runs.\n\n2. **Coconut Water**: A natural alternative that hydrates and provides potassium and electrolytes without added sugars.\n\n3. **Sports Drinks**: Products like Nuun or CLIF Shot Electrolyte Drink Mix are low in sugar and high in electrolytes, making them suitable for pre-run hydration.\n\n4. **Coffee or Caffeinated Drinks**: A moderate amount of caffeine can enhance performance and focus. Consider a cup of black coffee or a pre-workout drink containing caffeine. Just be cautious about how your body reacts to caffeine.\n\n5. **Homemade Smoothies**: A blend of fruits (like bananas or berries), a source of protein (yogurt or protein powder), and some greens can provide a balanced source of energy. Add some oats for extra carbohydrates if you have time to digest.\n\n6. **Carbohydrate-Rich Drink**: A drink containing simple carbohydrates, like a mixture of fruit juice (e.g., orange juice) diluted with water, can provide quick energy.\n\n7. **Water**: Staying hydrated is essential. If you only have a short time before your run, plain water can suffice, especially if you already have adequate hydration.\n\n### Timing\n- Aim to consume your pre-workout drink about 30-60 minutes before your run to allow time for digestion and energy absorption.\n\n### Personalization\nUltimately, the best drink will depend on how your body responds to different foods and beverages. It may take some experimentation during your training runs to find what works best for you.",
